Nadia López García, nueva coordinadora n: Nadia López García, INBAL's new National Literature Coordinator, is a Mixtec poet recognized for her work in indigenous languages and her international career. Among her achievements are the Cenzontle Award and a scholarship from the Foundation for Mexican Letters.
La escritora Margaret Atwood, de 84 años: Writer Margaret Atwood, 84, called artificial intelligence (AI) “a shitty poet” and said she doesn't worry about its impact on literature, although she believes young people should. Known for The Handmaid's Tale, Atwood is now working on a memoir where she only includes stupidities and catastrophes
Gabriela Cabezón Cámara ganó el Premio d: Gabriela Cabezón Cámara won the Sor Juana Inés de la Cruz Literature Prize 2024 for Las niñas del naranjel, which reinterprets the life of Catalina de Erauso and highlights marginalized voices. The award will be presented on December 4 at the Guadalajara International Book Fair. The award recognizes the work of women writers in the Hispanic world and is endowed with ten thousand dollars.
